You can write C# code to sort an unsorted array of integers using the quicksort algorithm. The algorithm works by choosing a pivot element from the array and partitioning the array into two subarrays such that all elements less than or equal to the pivot are in the left subarray and all elements greater than the pivot are in the right subarray. Then it recursively sorts the left and right subarrays until the array is sorted. Here is an example of how you can sort an array using the quicksort algorithm:

```
    // Sort unsorted array using quicksort algorithm
    // Input:  array - unsorted array of integers
    // Output:  array - sorted array of integers
    void SortArrayUsingQuicksort(int[] array)
    {
        if (array.Length <= 1)
            return;

        int pivot = array[0]; // Choose a pivot element from the array
        int left = 0; // Index of left subarray
        int right = array.Length - 1; // Index of right subarray

        while (left < right)
        {
            int i = left + (right - left) / 2; // Compute the index of the element to swap

            if (array[i] < pivot) // If the element to the left of the pivot is less than the pivot, swap it with the element to the right of the pivot
                exchange(array, left, i);
            else if (array[i] > pivot) // If the element to the right of the pivot is greater than the pivot, swap it with the element to the left of the pivot
                exchange(array, i, left);
            else // Elements are already in sorted order, exit the loop
                break;

            // Recursive call to sort the subarrays
            SortArrayUsingQuicksort(array, left, i - 1);
            SortArrayUsingQuicksort(array, i + 1, right);
        }

        // Swap the pivot element with the last element
        exchange(array, left, right - 1);
    }

    // Recursive helper function to swap two elements in an array
    void exchange(int[] array, int i, int j)
    {
        int tmp = array[i];
        array[i] = array[j];
        array[j] = tmp;
    }
```

